them, viz. repentance, faith and baptiſme ; in do‑ ing of which, they, to wit, ſo many as did repent of their ſheding the innocent blood, and were ac‑ cordingly baptized, did receive forgiveneſs, as Chri had prayed they ſhould ; but as for the re, all the blood that was ſhed upon the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel, unto the blood of Zacharias ſhall be upon them, yea, and the in nocent blood of Chri alſo, which they dered might be on them and their Children.
